    <Seg.RankDef>
        <defName>Seg_WOTV_Quartermaster</defName>
        <label>Quartermaster</label>
        <description>The ship's quartermaster is possibly the most important person on board, for without them the ship's crew would starve and even the most skilled enginarium clan would soon run out of spare parts to enact repairs. Quartermasters often dedicate themselves to finding every possible trick and loophole in securing the most effective technology and equipment the Imperium has to offer for the ship they serve on.</description>
        <rankIconPath>UI/Ranks/VoidshipCrew/Seg_WOTV_Quartermaster</rankIconPath>
        <colonyLimitOfRank>(1, 0)</colonyLimitOfRank>
        <rankTier>6</rankTier>
        <incompatibleRanks>
            <li>Seg_WOTV_MasterHelmsman</li>
            <li>Seg_WOTV_Voxmaster</li>
            <li>Seg_WOTV_Shipmaster</li>
            <li>Seg_WOTV_LordCaptain</li>
        </incompatibleRanks>
        <requiredSkills>
            <Social>7</Social>
            <Intellectual>5</Intellectual>			
        </requiredSkills>
        <statOffsets>
            <NegotiationAbility>0.20</NegotiationAbility>
            <ResearchSpeed>0.10</ResearchSpeed>
            <ReadingSpeed>0.20</ReadingSpeed>
        </statOffsets>
        <givesPassions>
            <li>
				<skill>Intellectual</skill>
				<modType>AddOneLevel</modType>
			</li>
        </givesPassions>
    </Seg.RankDef>
	
    <Seg.RankDef>
        <defName>Seg_WOTV_MasterHelmsman</defName>
        <label>Master Helmsman</label>
        <description>The master helmsman is responsible for directing the movement of the ship in realspace, and is required to understand the dynamics and forces of celestial bodies and how their gravity affects the voidship. The most skillful helmsmen can dance millions of tons of metal through vacuum like an Old Terran hummingbird darting around a flower.</description>
        <rankIconPath>UI/Ranks/VoidshipCrew/Seg_WOTV_MasterHelmsman</rankIconPath>
        <colonyLimitOfRank>(1, 0)</colonyLimitOfRank>
        <rankTier>6</rankTier>
        <incompatibleRanks>
            <li>Seg_WOTV_Quartermaster</li>
            <li>Seg_WOTV_Voxmaster</li>
            <li>Seg_WOTV_Shipmaster</li>
            <li>Seg_WOTV_LordCaptain</li>
        </incompatibleRanks>
        <requiredSkills>
            <Intellectual>5</Intellectual>
        </requiredSkills>
        <statOffsets>
            <PilotingAbility MayRequire="Ludeon.RimWorld.Odyssey"> 0.7</PilotingAbility>
            <MoveSpeed>0.05</MoveSpeed>
        </statOffsets>
    </Seg.RankDef>
	
     <Seg.RankDef>
        <defName>Seg_WOTV_Voxmaster</defName>
        <label>Voxmaster</label>
        <description>The ship's voxmaster is in charge of all shipboard communications as well as vox channels with other ships, stations, or facilities on-planet. Even the ship's astropaths will report warp-borne interstellar communications to the Voxmaster to pass on to the ship's commander.</description>
        <rankIconPath>UI/Ranks/VoidshipCrew/Seg_WOTV_Voxmaster</rankIconPath>
        <rankTier>6</rankTier>
        <colonyLimitOfRank>(1, 0)</colonyLimitOfRank>
        <incompatibleRanks>
            <li>Seg_WOTV_Quartermaster</li>
            <li>Seg_WOTV_MasterHelmsman</li>
            <li>Seg_WOTV_Shipmaster</li>
            <li>Seg_WOTV_LordCaptain</li>
        </incompatibleRanks>
        <requiredSkills>
            <Social>8</Social>
            <Intellectual>4</Intellectual>			
        </requiredSkills>
        <statOffsets>
            <SocialImpact>.50</SocialImpact>
            <ConversionPower MayRequire="Ludeon.RimWorld.Ideology">1.10</ConversionPower>
        </statOffsets>
    </Seg.RankDef>
	
     <Seg.RankDef>
        <defName>Seg_WOTV_Shipmaster</defName>
        <label>Shipmaster</label>
        <description>The Shipmaster is in command of the day to day operations of a voidship, issuing orders to subordinate officers to have their every command carried out, unless countermanded by a higher noble or senior naval officer.</description>
        <rankIconPath>UI/Ranks/VoidshipCrew/Seg_WOTV_Shipmaster</rankIconPath>
        <colonyLimitOfRank>(1, 0)</colonyLimitOfRank>
        <rankTier>7</rankTier>
        <incompatibleRanks>
            <li>Seg_WOTV_LordCaptain</li>
        </incompatibleRanks>
        <requiredSkills>
            <Social>10</Social>
        </requiredSkills>
        <statOffsets>
            <SocialImpact>0.20</SocialImpact>
            <NegotiationAbility>0.10</NegotiationAbility>
        </statOffsets>
        <removeRanksOnUnlock>
            <li>Seg_WOTV_Voxmaster</li>
            <li>Seg_WOTV_MasterHelmsman</li>
            <li>Seg_WOTV_Quartermaster</li>
        </removeRanksOnUnlock>
    </Seg.RankDef> 

    <Seg.RankDef>
        <defName>Seg_WOTV_LordCaptain</defName>
        <label>Lord Captain</label>
        <description>Lord Captain is a title given to a Rogue Trader in command of their own voidship. For their crew and sworn vassals, the Lord Captain's word is law no matter where they are. Many a Rogue Trader likes to adopt a swashbuckling style and sees themselves as a duellist or otherwise impressive combatant.</description>
        <rankIconPath>UI/Ranks/VoidshipCrew/Seg_WOTV_LordCaptain</rankIconPath>
        <colonyLimitOfRank>(1, 0)</colonyLimitOfRank>
        <rankTier>7</rankTier>
        <requiredSkills>
            <Social>14</Social>
        </requiredSkills>
        <statOffsets>
            <SocialImpact>0.50</SocialImpact>
            <NegotiationAbility>0.30</NegotiationAbility>
        </statOffsets>
         <statFactors>
           <NegotiationAbility>1.5</NegotiationAbility>
        </statFactors>
        <givesPassions>
            <li>
				<skill>Shooting</skill>
				<modType>AddOneLevel</modType>
			</li>
            <li>
				<skill>Melee</skill>
				<modType>AddOneLevel</modType>
			</li>
        </givesPassions>
        <removeRanksOnUnlock>
            <li>Seg_WOTV_Shipmaster</li>
        </removeRanksOnUnlock>
    </Seg.RankDef> 
    </Defs>